ن بِالرِّزْقِ الحَلالِ والطيب.","english":"Allah provides humans with lawful and good sustenance."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grant, to give; to provide with the means of subsistence, to provide for, to enrich"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grant, to give; to allot to, to bless with, to endow with"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grant, to give; to bestow on, to confer on"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to thank"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَزَقَ (razaqa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nMiddle Persian 𐭫𐭥𐭰𐭩𐭪 (rōzīg)der.\nArabic رزق\nDerived from Middle Persian 𐭫𐭥𐭰𐭩𐭪 (rōzīg, “daily bread, sustenance”). Compare Persian روزی (rôzi).\n\nEtymology tree\nMiddle Persian 𐭫𐭥𐭰𐭩𐭪 (rōzīg)der.\nArabic رِزْق (rizq)denom.\nArabic رزق\nDenominal verb from رِزْق (rizq)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n15396","headword_ar":"رِزْقٌ","root":"rzq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing whereby one profits,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from which one derives advantage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murotazaqN","text_ar":"مُرْتَزَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) in the pass. form: (TA: [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murotaziq","text_ar":"مُرْتَزِق"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a gift;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and especially, of God: (S:) or [especially, and according to general usage,] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means of subsistence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the support and growth of the body, which God sends to"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mankind and other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"animals;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sustenance, victuals, food,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"provisions;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a supply thereof from God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] but with the Moatezileh it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing possessed and eaten by the deserving;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that it does not apply to what is unlawful: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arozaAqN","text_ar":"اَرْزَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) and what are thus termed are of two kinds;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apparent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"material,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are for the bodies, such as aliments;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unapparent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intellectual,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are for the hearts and minds, such as the several sorts of knowledge and of science:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rizoqN","text_ar":"رِزْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"properly signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion, share,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or particularly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of something good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaZ~N","text_ar":"حَظٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and is conventionally made to apply to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing by which an animal is enabled to profit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in ii. 2:) and [hence] it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a daily allowance of food"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rizoqapN","text_ar":"رِزْقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1077},{"kind":"text","text":"which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rizaqN","text_ar":"رِزَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subsistencemoney, pay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allowance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a soldier; or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is given forth to the soldier at the commencement of every month,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"day by day:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to ElKarkhee,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaTaA='u","text_ar":"العَطَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is what is assigned to those who fight; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~azoqu","text_ar":"الرَّزْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the poor:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh: [but see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaTaA='N","text_ar":"عَطَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"razaqaAtN","text_ar":"رَزَقَاتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"razaqapN","text_ar":"رَزَقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the inf. n. of unity of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raraqa","text_ar":"رَرَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portions of subsistence-money, pay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allowances,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTomaAE","text_ar":"اَطْمَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of soldiers: (S, K:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamo rizoquka fiY Al$~ahori","text_ar":"كَمْ رِزْقُكَ فِى الشَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How much is thy allowance of food,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy subsistence-money,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the month?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*uwA A^arozaAqahumo","text_ar":"اَخَذُوا اَرْزَاقَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received, their portions of subsistence-money,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] (S, Msb, K) is said of soldiers. (S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~izoqu AlHasanu","text_ar":"الرِّزْقُ الحَسَنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"provision"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that comes to one without toil in the seeking thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"provision"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is found without one's looking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watching, for it, and without one's reckoning upon it, and without one's earning it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"labouring to earn it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT.) ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rain"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) is sometimes thus called; as in the Kur xlv. 4 and li. 22: this being an amplification in language; as when one says, “ The dates are in the bottom of the well; ” meaning thereby “ the [water for] watering the palm-trees. ” (S.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","Msb"]}]}}